<paragraph id="8BB198156475D730FC81FAEEFBBA0E4E" blockId="11.[828,1147,1327,1351]" box="[828,1147,1327,1351]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FC81FAEEFBDD0E4E" authority="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth, 2020" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" box="[828,1052,1327,1351]" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Myxococcus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="vastator" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FC81FAEEFBDD0E4E" box="[828,1052,1327,1351]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">Myxococcus vastator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A249F97C6475D730FB99FAEEFBBA0E4E" box="[1060,1147,1327,1351]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314CB9E6475D730FC81FA9AFABA0E9B" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB198156475D730FC81FA9AFABA0E9B" blockId="11.[828,1461,1371,1906]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FC81FA9AFBD30E7B" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" box="[828,1042,1371,1394]" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Myxococcus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="vastator">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FC81FA9AFBD30E7B" box="[828,1042,1371,1394]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">Myxococcus vastator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(vas.ta’tor L. masc. n. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FAB8FA9AFA970E7B" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" box="[1285,1366,1371,1394]" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Myxococcus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="vastator">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FAB8FA9AFA970E7B" box="[1285,1366,1371,1394]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">vastator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the ravager, after its ability to devastate colonies of prey cells).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314CB9E6475D730FCE4FA5AFBCE0C7B" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB198156475D730FCE4FA5AFC000DFB" blockId="11.[828,1461,1371,1906]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
Vegetative cells are Gram-negative bacilli tapering slightly at the ends, measuring 
<quantity id="4CF635F06475D730FB8DFA7AFB510EDB" box="[1072,1168,1466,1490]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.499999999999999" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" unit="m" value="0.6499999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.6">
0.6–0.7 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FB3EFA7BFB510EDB" bold="true" box="[1155,1168,1466,1490]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m 3.0–6.0 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FAA7FA7BFAE60EDB" bold="true" box="[1306,1319,1466,1490]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">m</emphasis>
m in electron micrographs. Colonies exhibit swarming motility and appear pale brown on VY-2 agar (w/v 0.5% dried baker’s yeast, 0.1% CaCl 
<subScript id="178A9A506475D730FC13F9E4FC790D3D" attach="left" box="[942,952,1573,1588]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">2</subScript>
2H 
<subScript id="178A9A506475D730FC60F9E4FC260D3D" attach="both" box="[989,999,1573,1588]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">2</subScript>
O, and 1.5% agar). Fruiting bodies are irregular spheroids, orange in color. Aerobic growth was observed at 30 C and at pH 8.0–9.0. Growth was unaffected by the addition of 1% NaCl. Hydrolyzes arginine and urea. Assimilates malate. Cells prey with low efficiency upon 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FC81F97AFC790DDB" authority="TOP" authorityName="TOP" box="[828,952,1723,1746]" class="Gammaproteobacteria" family="Enterobacteriaceae" genus="Escherichia" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Enterobacteriales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="coli">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FC81F97AFCBD0DDB" box="[828,892,1723,1746]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">E. coli</emphasis>
TOP
</taxonomicName>
10, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FC60F97AFB030DDB" authority="DSM" authorityName="DSM" box="[989,1218,1723,1746]" class="Actinobacteria" family="Microbacteriaceae" genus="Clavibacter" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Actinomycetales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Actinobacteria" rank="species" species="nebraskensis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FC60F97AFB440DDB" box="[989,1157,1723,1746]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">Cl. nebraskensis</emphasis>
DSM
</taxonomicName>
7483, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FAFAF97AFCAE0DFB" authority="DSM" authorityName="DSM" class="Ustilaginomycetes" family="Ustilaginaceae" genus="Ustilago" kingdom="Chromista" order="Ustilaginales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="maydis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FAFAF97AFA710DDB" box="[1351,1456,1723,1746]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">U. maydis</emphasis>
<accessionNumber id="945D05F66475D730FC81F91AFC7F0DFB" box="[828,958,1755,1778]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/DSM14603" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">DSM 14603</accessionNumber>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
